    "body": "ACK https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19281/commits/bb44fd944d4d7715aa1247d53da9ae21c59c543a\r\n\r\n- I've ran it against https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/2059d32edbd0ac8e4534b00243385b9fc2a2f3a4 with `--failfast` and forcing tests to fail. It properly triggered `SIGTERM` and processes were stopped gracefully as expected.\r\n- I've also tested sending an external `SIGTERM` to a running test and it was properly handled showing `Test cancelled` message.\r\n\r\nTested on OSX 11.1",
